{
  "text": "To determine the effects of bacterial DNA immunization on murine lupus, we first assessed serological findings of female NZB/NZW mice immunized with either EC dsDNA complexes with mBSA, CT dsDNA complexes with mBSA, or mBSA alone in adjuvant. Mice of this strain develop a genetically determined syndrome at 5-6 mo of age that resembles SLE in the occurrence of anti-DNA and immune complex-mediated renal disease [CITATION_1] . In confirmation of previous results, we found that 8-wk-old NZB/NZW mice immunized with EC dsDNA/mBSA complexes develop a prompt anti-dsDNA response that includes autoantibodies that bind CT as well as EC dsDNA [CITATION_2] . In contrast, NZB/NZW mice immunized with CT dsDNA/ mBSA or mBSA alone lacked significant antibody production (Fig. 1) .",
  "correct_citation": {
